article.headline: Creighton 76, Oregon State 75
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Amy Hoffman scored off an inbounds pass
from Christy Erickson with 25 seconds left to give Creighton a
76-75 victory over Oregon State on Thursday.

Oregon State had two chances to win in the final seconds. Casey
Bunn missed two free throws with 2.9 seconds remaining. Following a
jump ball, Shannon Howell missed a 15-foot shot at the buzzer.

Hoffman's basket provided the only points for Creighton (3-2) in
the last six minutes. Oregon State (2-3) scored only six points
during that stretch, but it was enough to erase a 74-69 deficit.

The game was a rematch of a Women's NIT quarterfinal last season
in Omaha, Neb. Creighton won that game 74-64.

Laura Spanheimer led the Bluejays with 31 points. She hit 6-of-7
shots in the first half, including 4-of-4 from 3-point range.

Howell led Oregon State with 26 points. Kim Butler added 22
points and eight rebounds.
